WEBVTT

1
00:00:09.052 --> 00:00:10.357
[Boyd] Previously onFrom...

2
00:00:10.488 --> 00:00:12.359
If these voices are real.

3
00:00:12.490 --> 00:00:14.318
if something here is
communicating with you.

4
00:00:14.448 --> 00:00:16.015
then that means you're
connected to this place

5
00:00:16.146 --> 00:00:17.538
in a way that
no one else here is.

6
00:00:17.669 --> 00:00:18.496
But we need proof.

7
00:00:18.626 --> 00:00:20.019
What is this?

8
00:00:20.150 --> 00:00:22.282
[Sara] They said they
watched you bury the bag

9
00:00:22.413 --> 00:00:24.937
and that this is proof
that they're real.

10
00:00:25.068 --> 00:00:26.504
Do you know what that means?

11
00:00:26.634 --> 00:00:27.722
[Trudy]
Can I have my pillow back?

12
00:00:27.853 --> 00:00:29.594
I just want to take a nap

13
00:00:29.724 --> 00:00:31.683
and it's sort of like a security
blanket for me. you know?

14
00:00:31.813 --> 00:00:34.599
Yeah. I totally get it.
I'm sorry again.

15
00:00:34.729 --> 00:00:37.645
You know. it's kinda funny.
I have a shirt just like that.

16
00:00:37.776 --> 00:00:39.691
Oh. I know.
I got this out of your suitcase.

17
00:00:39.821 --> 00:00:41.867
What's wrong?

18
00:00:41.997 --> 00:00:44.130
I think maybe
I-I made a mistake.

19
00:00:44.261 --> 00:00:46.698
I knew all about the divorce
and how this whole trip

20
00:00:46.828 --> 00:00:48.091
was just one last hurrah

21
00:00:48.221 --> 00:00:49.875
before you sat us down
to break the news.

22
00:00:50.005 --> 00:00:53.270
Thomas is dead!
You have two other kids!

23
00:00:53.400 --> 00:00:54.619
Why aren't we enough for you?

24
00:00:56.882 --> 00:00:57.926
What is that?

25
00:00:58.057 --> 00:00:59.537
A Farway Tree.

26
00:00:59.667 --> 00:01:00.842
Watch.

27
00:01:02.061 --> 00:01:04.281
How does it do that?

28
00:01:04.411 --> 00:01:05.630
I don't know.
But guess what.

29
00:01:05.760 --> 00:01:08.154
-What?
-It works for people too.

30
00:01:08.285 --> 00:01:09.938
Really?

31
00:01:10.069 --> 00:01:12.811
Problem is. you never know
where you'll end up.

32
00:01:12.941 --> 00:01:14.378
There's no wire in here.

33
00:01:14.508 --> 00:01:15.727
What?

34
00:01:15.857 --> 00:01:18.556
In the cord. And the plug?

35
00:01:18.686 --> 00:01:21.602
Look.
None of it makes any sense.

36
00:01:22.864 --> 00:01:24.562
[Hammering]

37
00:01:24.692 --> 00:01:25.911
[Ethan] Mom!

38
00:01:26.041 --> 00:01:27.608
Everything about
this is impossible.

39
00:01:27.739 --> 00:01:30.133
but we can find out
where those wires go.

40
00:01:34.093 --> 00:01:36.965
-[Screams]
-[Gasps]

41
00:01:37.096 --> 00:01:39.881
There was this weird fucking
symbol right on the ceiling!

42
00:01:40.012 --> 00:01:42.145
What are you looking for? Hmm?

43
00:01:46.671 --> 00:01:48.629
[Breathing unsteadily]

44
00:01:48.760 --> 00:01:50.805
I have this crazy idea that
might actually work. and--

45
00:01:50.936 --> 00:01:52.938
and if it does.

46
00:01:53.068 --> 00:01:55.636
I might be able to find a way
to get these people home.

47
00:01:57.986 --> 00:02:00.641
They're so beautiful.

48
00:02:02.643 --> 00:02:04.950
I'm so glad you like them.

49
00:02:05.080 --> 00:02:07.648
When can I come inside?

50
00:02:12.262 --> 00:02:14.873
[Indistinct conversations
overlapping]

51
00:02:20.270 --> 00:02:22.272
[Woman]
It's actually kind of rude.

52
00:02:22.402 --> 00:02:23.969
[Woman 2] I know.

53
00:02:24.099 --> 00:02:26.798
What? Not acceptable.
No way.

54
00:02:26.928 --> 00:02:33.370
[Chattering]

55
00:02:33.500 --> 00:02:35.850
Oh. let's not make a big deal.

56
00:02:35.981 --> 00:02:39.158
[Chattering]

57
00:02:39.289 --> 00:02:40.899
[Woman] It's a party.
you guys. like...

58
00:02:41.029 --> 00:02:44.076
[Chattering. laughing]

59
00:02:44.207 --> 00:02:46.557
-Okay. pick one.
-Um. this one.

60
00:02:48.820 --> 00:02:50.996
I don't know.
it just seems kinda weird

61
00:02:51.126 --> 00:02:53.128
to be celebrating the day
that you got stuck here.

62
00:02:53.259 --> 00:02:54.826
You're looking
at this the wrong way.

63
00:02:54.956 --> 00:02:56.871
It's about celebrating survival.

64
00:02:58.830 --> 00:03:00.919
It reminds everybody
that it's possible.

65
00:03:01.049 --> 00:03:05.010
Besides. it's nice having
a little party once in a while.

66
00:03:06.533 --> 00:03:08.796
Okay. what are you looking for?

67
00:03:08.927 --> 00:03:11.538
I am not looking.
I am digging.

68
00:03:11.669 --> 00:03:14.628
Aha! Here it is.

69
00:03:14.759 --> 00:03:16.239
It's my secret stash.

70
00:03:19.067 --> 00:03:23.246
Trudy loves this sweater.

71
00:03:23.376 --> 00:03:26.640
It's the one thing I own that I
don't let her get her hands on.

72
00:03:26.771 --> 00:03:29.643
Besides. it is Ellis' favorite.

73
00:03:34.169 --> 00:03:35.606
What?

74
00:03:35.736 --> 00:03:38.696
Nothing.
Uh...

75
00:03:38.826 --> 00:03:42.090
You just-- you make this
place seem almost normal.

76
00:03:42.221 --> 00:03:44.484
You're really special.

77
00:03:44.615 --> 00:03:46.834
Don't be silly.
We're all really special.

78
00:03:46.965 --> 00:03:49.272
Even Trudy.

79
00:03:49.402 --> 00:03:51.665
That's something a really
special person would say.

80
00:03:56.844 --> 00:03:58.933
There's my girls.

81
00:03:59.064 --> 00:04:00.718
Uh. anybody up
for a little pregame?

82
00:04:00.848 --> 00:04:02.807
Baby. the party hasn't
even started yet.

83
00:04:02.937 --> 00:04:06.550
I know! I know!
That's why they call it pregame.

84
00:04:07.899 --> 00:04:08.769
What?

85
00:04:10.771 --> 00:04:11.946
Nothing.

86
00:04:12.077 --> 00:04:14.688
Just... go easy. okay?

87
00:04:14.819 --> 00:04:15.994
Yeah. I know.
I know. I know.

88
00:04:17.778 --> 00:04:18.866
Uh. Julie?

89
00:04:18.997 --> 00:04:20.868
How 'bout you?

90
00:04:20.999 --> 00:04:23.784
Uh... I'm good. thanks.

91
00:04:23.915 --> 00:04:25.699
Okay.

92
00:04:25.830 --> 00:04:28.746
Okay. whatever.
You guys suck.

93
00:04:28.876 --> 00:04:31.488
Victor?
Victor. where you at. man?

94
00:04:31.618 --> 00:04:33.098
Let's get this party started!

95
00:04:33.228 --> 00:04:35.013
Is he okay?

96
00:04:36.057 --> 00:04:39.278
Nights like this are just
a little tough for him.

97
00:04:39.409 --> 00:04:41.236
As much as you celebrate
the people who make it.

98
00:04:41.367 --> 00:04:43.717
you also remember
the ones who didn't.

99
00:04:47.025 --> 00:04:49.723
Here. you should wear this.
It'll look really cute.

100
00:04:57.949 --> 00:04:59.211
Okay. come on. man.

101
00:04:59.342 --> 00:05:01.779
I mean. you of all people
should be hammered today.

102
00:05:01.909 --> 00:05:02.997
I mean. how many years
have you been here for?

103
00:05:03.128 --> 00:05:04.825
Please leave me alone.

104
00:05:04.956 --> 00:05:06.871
-Oh...
-[Donna] Ellis!

105
00:05:07.001 --> 00:05:08.002
Ellis!

106
00:05:10.048 --> 00:05:11.528
You want a shot?

107
00:05:13.007 --> 00:05:14.531
Okay.

108
00:05:17.882 --> 00:05:19.884
Donna. there's no more peaches.

109
00:05:20.014 --> 00:05:22.800
I know. We're. uh...

110
00:05:22.930 --> 00:05:24.932
We're all out.

111
00:05:25.063 --> 00:05:27.108
They're gone?

112
00:05:27.239 --> 00:05:28.849
I thought I had a few more cans
stashed away in the basement.

113
00:05:28.980 --> 00:05:30.895
but. uh...

114
00:05:31.025 --> 00:05:33.941
I've been putting some
other things aside for you.

115
00:05:34.072 --> 00:05:35.900
Some fruit cocktail.
Some cranberries--

116
00:05:36.030 --> 00:05:38.250
The peaches are gone.

117
00:05:38.381 --> 00:05:40.208
All these years. that's--

118
00:05:40.339 --> 00:05:42.080
that's the one thing
that's never changed.

119
00:05:42.210 --> 00:05:44.909
and now they're gone.

120
00:05:45.039 --> 00:05:47.041
I'm sorry. Victor.

121
00:05:47.172 --> 00:05:48.956
[Victor] Yeah.

122
00:06:06.365 --> 00:06:08.846
[Woman] Kevin. come on!
It'll be dark soon.

123
00:06:08.976 --> 00:06:10.021
Coming.

124
00:06:10.151 --> 00:06:11.588
[Door closing]

125
00:06:11.718 --> 00:06:17.724
♪

126
00:06:20.248 --> 00:06:24.862
["Que Sera. Sera [Whatever Will
Be. Will be]" plays]

127
00:06:24.992 --> 00:06:30.215
♪

128
00:06:30.345 --> 00:06:35.046
♪ When I was
just a little boy♪

129
00:06:35.176 --> 00:06:37.309
♪ I asked my father♪

130
00:06:37.440 --> 00:06:39.790
♪ "What will I be?"♪

131
00:06:41.269 --> 00:06:43.576
♪ "Will I be handsome?"♪

132
00:06:43.707 --> 00:06:46.057
♪ "Will I be rich?"♪

133
00:06:46.187 --> 00:06:49.147
♪ Here's what he said to me♪

134
00:06:50.235 --> 00:06:53.368
♪ "Que sera. sera"♪

135
00:06:53.499 --> 00:06:57.068
♪ "Whatever will be. will be"♪

136
00:07:00.071 --> 00:07:03.161
♪ "The future's
Not ours to see"♪

137
00:07:03.291 --> 00:07:06.860
♪ "Que sera. sera"♪

138
00:07:08.340 --> 00:07:11.038
♪ "What will be. will be"♪

139
00:07:21.092 --> 00:07:25.357
♪ Now
I have children of my own♪

140
00:07:25.488 --> 00:07:28.055
♪ They ask their father♪

141
00:07:28.186 --> 00:07:30.144
♪ "What will I be?♪

142
00:07:32.016 --> 00:07:34.192
♪ "Will I be pretty?"♪

143
00:07:34.322 --> 00:07:36.368
♪ "Will I be rich?"♪

144
00:07:36.499 --> 00:07:38.979
♪ I tell them tenderly♪

145
00:07:41.504 --> 00:07:44.158
♪ "Que sera. sera"♪

146
00:07:44.289 --> 00:07:49.163
♪ "Whatever will be. will be"♪

147
00:07:49.294 --> 00:07:53.994
♪ "The future's
Not ours to see"♪

148
00:07:54.125 --> 00:07:56.170
♪ "Que sera. sera"♪

149
00:07:59.217 --> 00:08:01.785
♪ "What will be. will be"♪

150
00:08:04.048 --> 00:08:06.006
♪ "Que sera. sera"♪

151
00:08:22.283 --> 00:08:26.853
-[Bell ringing]
-[Indistinct conversation]

152
00:08:26.984 --> 00:08:31.771
[Bell ringing]

153
00:08:34.774 --> 00:08:39.736
[Bell ringing]

154
00:08:39.866 --> 00:08:41.389
"There was so much joy
on the faces

155
00:08:41.520 --> 00:08:44.349
"of all the new wondrous
friends she had made.

156
00:08:44.479 --> 00:08:47.221
"so much magic in all the
marvelous places she had been.

157
00:08:47.352 --> 00:08:50.007
[Bell ringing]

158
00:08:50.137 --> 00:08:52.357
"Yet the Cromenockle
had a feeling

159
00:08:52.487 --> 00:08:54.359
"there was still
more yet to come.

160
00:08:54.489 --> 00:08:58.015
"and that her adventures
in this strange new world

161
00:08:58.145 --> 00:09:00.147
truly had just only begun."

162
00:09:00.278 --> 00:09:03.803
[Bell ringing in distance]

163
00:09:03.934 --> 00:09:13.900
♪

164
00:09:36.575 --> 00:09:38.359
[Knocking]
Jade?

165
00:09:41.319 --> 00:09:43.190
[Jade]
I say you could come in?

166
00:09:43.321 --> 00:09:45.236
My mom wants us
to get dinner started.

167
00:09:45.366 --> 00:09:47.630
Come on.

168
00:09:47.760 --> 00:09:50.502
-What are you doing?
-What the hell. man?

169
00:09:50.633 --> 00:09:53.418
-I was reading this!
-There's no other paper here!

170
00:09:53.548 --> 00:09:56.247
That doesn't mean start drawing
in my fucking book.

171
00:09:56.377 --> 00:09:58.466
You want me to write
on your walls?

172
00:09:58.597 --> 00:10:00.120
Like a psychopath?!

173
00:10:04.124 --> 00:10:08.302
[Indistinct chattering]

174
00:10:12.393 --> 00:10:15.135
What are you doing out here?

175
00:10:15.266 --> 00:10:18.312
I. uh. think there's some
things we need to talk about.

176
00:10:19.400 --> 00:10:21.185
In private.

177
00:10:21.315 --> 00:10:23.143
All right.
come by in the morning.

178
00:10:23.274 --> 00:10:26.016
No. I think we should
do this now.

179
00:10:26.146 --> 00:10:27.887
It's important.

180
00:10:31.717 --> 00:10:33.937
I guess we're having
a sleepover then.

181
00:10:36.156 --> 00:10:37.244
Come on in.

182
00:10:42.685 --> 00:10:45.339
[Door closing. lock clicking]

183
00:10:50.431 --> 00:10:52.346
Looks like you're
going somewhere.

184
00:10:52.477 --> 00:10:57.221
Yeah. I was gonna come by and
talk to you about all this.

185
00:10:57.351 --> 00:10:59.702
Well. we have more to
talk about than I thought.

186
00:11:04.445 --> 00:11:05.490
[Tabitha sighs]

187
00:11:05.620 --> 00:11:08.406
He's completely passed out.

188
00:11:08.536 --> 00:11:10.364
Well. pretty sure

189
00:11:10.495 --> 00:11:12.366
you violated
about a dozen child labor laws

190
00:11:12.497 --> 00:11:15.239
by having him dig
in the basement all day.

191
00:11:15.369 --> 00:11:17.981
No. he was having fun.
He just wanted to help.

192
00:11:21.898 --> 00:11:24.422
I get so nervous every time
I take my eyes off him.

193
00:11:24.552 --> 00:11:27.207
Yeah.
Yeah. me too.

194
00:11:27.338 --> 00:11:31.385
But. look.
windows are nailed shut.

195
00:11:31.516 --> 00:11:34.432
The doors are locked.

196
00:11:34.562 --> 00:11:36.347
He couldn't let one
of those things in if he tried.

197
00:11:36.477 --> 00:11:38.349
Yeah. yeah.

198
00:11:40.830 --> 00:11:43.746
Fuck! And then I think about
Julie up in that house.

199
00:11:43.876 --> 00:11:47.010
Donna. the lady who runs
the place. she might be a...

200
00:11:47.140 --> 00:11:49.664
[Chuckles]

201
00:11:49.795 --> 00:11:52.015
...but she's
definitely not stupid.

202
00:11:52.145 --> 00:11:52.929
Yeah.

203
00:11:54.408 --> 00:11:56.497
How's it going?

204
00:11:56.628 --> 00:11:58.325
Well...

205
00:11:58.456 --> 00:12:00.284
provided I can
convince the sheriff

206
00:12:00.414 --> 00:12:02.677
to let me use all of
their building materials.

207
00:12:02.808 --> 00:12:05.550
not to mention drain every
single battery they've got.

208
00:12:05.680 --> 00:12:07.334
and get Donna
to allow us to build

209
00:12:07.465 --> 00:12:09.162
on the high ground
at Colony House.

210
00:12:09.293 --> 00:12:10.424
should be just promising enough

211
00:12:10.555 --> 00:12:12.644
for everyone to hate me
when it fails.

212
00:12:12.775 --> 00:12:14.254
Oh. come on.
don't say that.

213
00:12:14.385 --> 00:12:15.952
You got a signal.

214
00:12:16.082 --> 00:12:18.302
No. come on.
I got static.

215
00:12:18.432 --> 00:12:20.434
That's a far cry from a signal.

216
00:12:20.565 --> 00:12:22.175
Well. but it's something.

217
00:12:23.611 --> 00:12:25.178
Yeah.

218
00:12:27.702 --> 00:12:30.183
Hey. Hey.

219
00:12:32.707 --> 00:12:35.580
It matters.

220
00:12:35.710 --> 00:12:37.538
And look.
look on the bright side.

221
00:12:37.669 --> 00:12:39.366
at least we've got our hole in
the basement to fall back on.

222
00:12:39.497 --> 00:12:40.585
Or in.

223
00:12:40.715 --> 00:12:43.196
Or in.
I'm gonna head back down.

224
00:12:45.416 --> 00:12:47.113
Best get to it.

225
00:12:52.379 --> 00:12:56.340
-[Music playing]
-[Indistinct chatter. laughter]

226
00:12:56.470 --> 00:12:58.255
Oh. shit.

227
00:12:58.385 --> 00:13:00.213
Hey. watch where
you're going. man. Fuck.

228
00:13:00.344 --> 00:13:02.476
Hey. hey. hey.
Hey! Hold on.

229
00:13:02.607 --> 00:13:04.217
-Hey.
-Maybe slow down a little bit.

230
00:13:04.348 --> 00:13:05.653
Hey. I'm-- I'm fine.
I'm fine.

231
00:13:05.784 --> 00:13:07.481
It's a party. right?

232
00:13:07.612 --> 00:13:09.483
Don't worry.

233
00:13:12.617 --> 00:13:14.532
Is everything okay?

234
00:13:14.662 --> 00:13:16.664
Yeah. I think so.

235
00:13:16.795 --> 00:13:18.710
He said not to worry.
so I'm going to worry.

236
00:13:18.841 --> 00:13:22.583
[Donna] All right.
everybody settle down now!

237
00:13:22.714 --> 00:13:24.324
-Everybody!
-We should go.

238
00:13:24.455 --> 00:13:25.586
[Julie] Yeah. yeah. yes.

239
00:13:25.717 --> 00:13:29.329
Hey. shut your fucking mouths!

240
00:13:29.460 --> 00:13:31.331
[All laughing]

241
00:13:31.462 --> 00:13:33.377
All right.

242
00:13:33.507 --> 00:13:35.683
We are here tonight

243
00:13:35.814 --> 00:13:39.165
to celebrate a very
special anniversary.

244
00:13:39.296 --> 00:13:40.558
[Woman] Yeah.

245
00:13:40.688 --> 00:13:42.342
One year ago today...

246
00:13:45.563 --> 00:13:48.174
...our dear sweet Fatima
came into our lives.

247
00:13:48.305 --> 00:13:49.480
[Light cheering]

248
00:13:49.610 --> 00:13:51.221
Some of you were here then.

249
00:13:51.351 --> 00:13:54.311
many of you arrived since.

250
00:13:55.007 --> 00:13:58.532
But all of you have
come to know her

251
00:13:58.663 --> 00:14:00.317
and to love her.

252
00:14:00.447 --> 00:14:04.538
for her kindness.
for her strength.

253
00:14:04.669 --> 00:14:05.539
for her wisdom--

254
00:14:05.670 --> 00:14:07.193
And for her weed!

255
00:14:07.324 --> 00:14:10.718
[All laughing]

256
00:14:10.849 --> 00:14:13.417
The green thumb is
definitely a big plus.

257
00:14:13.547 --> 00:14:14.853
[Laugh]

258
00:14:14.984 --> 00:14:17.377
Our greenhouse
never smelled so good.

259
00:14:17.508 --> 00:14:19.553
[Laugh]

260
00:14:19.684 --> 00:14:22.426
But. uh. seriously.

261
00:14:22.556 --> 00:14:25.820
the truth is...

262
00:14:25.951 --> 00:14:28.475
you've made this big
old drafty box

263
00:14:28.606 --> 00:14:29.694
feel a little bit
more like home.

264
00:14:31.783 --> 00:14:34.525
Happy anniversary. sweet pea.

265
00:14:34.655 --> 00:14:36.527
Donna...

266
00:14:39.791 --> 00:14:41.184
Thank you.

267
00:14:49.714 --> 00:14:51.498
This is so beautiful.

268
00:14:53.544 --> 00:14:55.589
May it catch
all the bad dreams...

269
00:14:57.722 --> 00:15:00.377
...and let only
the sweet ones reach you.

270
00:15:02.422 --> 00:15:03.946
-Come here.
-Thank you.

271
00:15:05.773 --> 00:15:10.430
Oh. We are so lucky to have you.

272
00:15:10.561 --> 00:15:12.302
So lucky to have...

273
00:15:13.172 --> 00:15:15.479
-All right with the mushy.
-[Laughs]

274
00:15:15.609 --> 00:15:18.438
All right. everybody.
you all know the protocol.

275
00:15:18.569 --> 00:15:21.659
Drink. smoke. have fun.

276
00:15:21.789 --> 00:15:24.618
keep an eye on each other.

277
00:15:24.749 --> 00:15:26.446
-Cheers!
-[All] Cheers.

278
00:15:26.577 --> 00:15:27.708
Cheers. baby.

279
00:15:27.839 --> 00:15:31.451
-[Chattering]
-[Music playing]

280
00:15:31.582 --> 00:15:33.323
Happy anniversary. gorgeous.

281
00:15:33.453 --> 00:15:34.585
Thank you.

282
00:15:45.639 --> 00:15:48.468
Look at what
she got me.

283
00:15:48.599 --> 00:15:49.774
She made this herself.

284
00:15:49.904 --> 00:15:52.559
[Stacey] Aw!

285
00:15:52.690 --> 00:15:54.953
So. that's the plan. Yup.

286
00:15:55.084 --> 00:15:56.999
Find a way outta here
once and for all

287
00:15:57.129 --> 00:16:00.263
before it all comes
crashing down around us.

288
00:16:02.917 --> 00:16:04.441
Your turn.

289
00:16:09.750 --> 00:16:12.666
I buried this bag
the day I arrived.

290
00:16:16.627 --> 00:16:18.194
Open it.

291
00:16:24.809 --> 00:16:26.332
Holding out on me?

292
00:16:30.771 --> 00:16:32.425
This yours?

293
00:16:35.080 --> 00:16:38.779
I'm not talking about the shirt.
I'm talking about the blood.

294
00:16:38.910 --> 00:16:40.259
There's another item in the bag.

295
00:16:45.221 --> 00:16:48.050
I mean. what-- what is it?
What the fuck is going on?

296
00:16:51.792 --> 00:16:54.882
We've never really
discussed who we used to be...

297
00:16:55.013 --> 00:16:58.538
before we came here.

298
00:17:01.976 --> 00:17:04.240
[Exhales]

299
00:17:08.026 --> 00:17:12.552
There was this young boy
in my congregation.

300
00:17:12.683 --> 00:17:16.861
He was quiet. sensitive.

301
00:17:18.776 --> 00:17:20.734
He used to get so excited

302
00:17:20.865 --> 00:17:22.736
when his mother let him put a
dollar in the collection plate.

303
00:17:26.740 --> 00:17:28.916
One day. after mass.

304
00:17:29.047 --> 00:17:32.398
I found him lingering
outside the rectory

305
00:17:32.529 --> 00:17:35.575
and it was unusual.

306
00:17:37.838 --> 00:17:39.275
You know. he wasn't
really the type of kid

307
00:17:39.405 --> 00:17:40.711
to stray too far
from his parents.

308
00:17:40.841 --> 00:17:43.627
They were very. um...

309
00:17:43.757 --> 00:17:45.672
strict...

310
00:17:47.718 --> 00:17:50.895
...rigid.

311
00:17:51.025 --> 00:17:54.986
And I get it. Parents.
they worry about their kids.

312
00:17:55.117 --> 00:17:57.771
and sometimes you have...

313
00:17:58.903 --> 00:18:01.688
[Exhales]

314
00:18:01.819 --> 00:18:03.734
I'm sorry.
Do you mind?

315
00:18:03.864 --> 00:18:05.301
[Exhales]

316
00:18:10.871 --> 00:18:13.004
[Gasps]

317
00:18:13.135 --> 00:18:17.661
Anyway. the point is...

318
00:18:17.791 --> 00:18:19.532
the boy was upset.

319
00:18:21.795 --> 00:18:23.797
He asked if he
could stay a while.

320
00:18:23.928 --> 00:18:26.931
But I had to prepare
for evening mass

321
00:18:27.061 --> 00:18:31.631
and I didn't want
the parents to worry.

322
00:18:33.851 --> 00:18:37.637
So I. uh...

323
00:18:37.768 --> 00:18:40.814
I went to my drawer and
I pulled out a candy bar.

324
00:18:40.945 --> 00:18:45.515
I. uh-- I always keep a stash
for the neighborhood kids.

325
00:18:48.474 --> 00:18:51.173
I could see he
didn't want to go.

326
00:18:53.131 --> 00:18:58.180
But I handed it to him
and I sent him on his way.

327
00:19:02.314 --> 00:19:06.753
Later that evening. I.
uh-- I went by the house.

328
00:19:10.104 --> 00:19:12.019
It was a bit unorthodox.

329
00:19:12.150 --> 00:19:15.806
You know. I'm not really in
the habit of making house calls.

330
00:19:15.936 --> 00:19:18.896
but something was
nagging me and I just...

331
00:19:21.681 --> 00:19:22.987
As I walked up the driveway.

332
00:19:23.117 --> 00:19:25.642
the mother.
she came running out.

333
00:19:25.772 --> 00:19:29.863
hysterical...

334
00:19:29.994 --> 00:19:32.475
inconsolable.

335
00:19:32.605 --> 00:19:34.390
She was...

336
00:19:37.915 --> 00:19:39.438
And I could smell the alcohol

337
00:19:39.569 --> 00:19:41.484
the moment I stepped
through the door.

338
00:19:42.702 --> 00:19:45.879
The father was just...

339
00:19:46.010 --> 00:19:47.838
standing there
with this panicked.

340
00:19:47.968 --> 00:19:49.970
dumbfounded look on his face.

341
00:19:50.101 --> 00:19:53.539
"Get up! Get up!" he said.

342
00:19:57.282 --> 00:20:01.852
I walked over and I stepped in
the room. and there he was.

343
00:20:04.942 --> 00:20:09.686
This sweet. innocent boy.

344
00:20:09.816 --> 00:20:14.734
just laying there. broken.

345
00:20:14.865 --> 00:20:18.260
His neck was bulging in a way--
it was...

346
00:20:22.786 --> 00:20:26.572
And I could see.
in his pocket...

347
00:20:26.703 --> 00:20:28.661
the candy bar.

348
00:20:30.707 --> 00:20:32.665
[Exhales unsteadily]

349
00:20:34.232 --> 00:20:37.279
"He'll be fine."

350
00:20:37.409 --> 00:20:39.759
That's what the father said.
"He'll be fine."

351
00:20:41.108 --> 00:20:43.763
It was the way he said it.

352
00:20:43.894 --> 00:20:45.591
Sounded indignant.

353
00:20:48.899 --> 00:20:53.033
The next thing I knew.
I was on top of him.

354
00:20:53.164 --> 00:20:55.949
smashing his face
as hard as I could.

355
00:20:56.080 --> 00:20:58.778
I couldn't stop.

356
00:20:58.909 --> 00:21:00.867
I just kept hitting
him over and over again.

357
00:21:00.998 --> 00:21:02.913
I couldn't stop.

358
00:21:03.043 --> 00:21:05.785
Even when I felt the bones
in my hand start to break.

359
00:21:05.916 --> 00:21:06.873
I couldn't stop.

360
00:21:10.268 --> 00:21:14.141
I was the one
who was supposed to listen.

361
00:21:14.272 --> 00:21:18.015
I was the one who was supposed
to defend the defenseless.

362
00:21:18.145 --> 00:21:21.975
That sweet little boy came
to me begging for help.

363
00:21:22.106 --> 00:21:24.587
and all I could do was
give him a candy bar.

364
00:21:26.066 --> 00:21:28.591
A fucking candy bar!

365
00:21:37.077 --> 00:21:39.993
The next thing I remember.

366
00:21:40.124 --> 00:21:42.866
I was standing on a bridge.
holding that bottle in my hand.

367
00:21:42.996 --> 00:21:44.737
And it was the first time
in my life

368
00:21:44.868 --> 00:21:46.609
that I heard the voice of God.

369
00:21:48.393 --> 00:21:50.134
He told me to get
back in the car.

370
00:21:50.264 --> 00:21:52.615
that there was another
path for me to follow.

371
00:21:53.790 --> 00:21:56.140
So I did.

372
00:21:56.270 --> 00:21:57.794
I got back in the car
and I drove.

373
00:21:57.924 --> 00:21:59.752
and two hours later. I was here.

374
00:22:05.279 --> 00:22:07.064
Why are you
telling me all this now?

375
00:22:10.197 --> 00:22:12.852
Because I have Sara tied up in
the basement of the church.

376
00:22:15.159 --> 00:22:17.335
Look. I've always known that
there's a reason we're here.

377
00:22:17.466 --> 00:22:19.032
that there's a path
we're meant to follow.

378
00:22:19.163 --> 00:22:20.033
and I know it may seem--

379
00:22:20.164 --> 00:22:21.731
[Gun cocking]

380
00:22:21.861 --> 00:22:23.733
Tell me you're joking.

381
00:22:23.863 --> 00:22:25.169
Boyd--

382
00:22:25.299 --> 00:22:26.953
Tell me you are
motherfucking joking!

383
00:22:27.084 --> 00:22:28.564
Are you gonna shoot me?

384
00:22:28.694 --> 00:22:30.043
I might fucking shoot you. yeah!

385
00:22:30.174 --> 00:22:32.263
You told me that
Frank broke the rules.

386
00:22:32.394 --> 00:22:34.178
Frank had to go in the box!

387
00:22:34.308 --> 00:22:36.267
And now you just--
that girl--

388
00:22:36.398 --> 00:22:38.661
That girl may be the key
to unlocking all this.

389
00:22:40.010 --> 00:22:41.228
That girl...

390
00:22:41.359 --> 00:22:43.796
may be the way we all go home.

391
00:22:45.189 --> 00:22:47.844
Keep talking.

392
00:22:47.974 --> 00:22:49.236
Okay.

393
00:22:49.367 --> 00:22:53.066
[Indistinct chatter]

394
00:23:04.991 --> 00:23:06.079
Jasmine.

395
00:23:07.211 --> 00:23:08.691
[Tapping]

396
00:23:08.821 --> 00:23:09.909
Jasmine!

397
00:23:10.040 --> 00:23:11.607
What's wrong?

398
00:23:12.912 --> 00:23:14.871
I only came to say goodbye.

399
00:23:15.001 --> 00:23:16.873
What?
Wait. wait. wait.

400
00:23:17.003 --> 00:23:20.703
I don't understand.
Just please talk to me.

401
00:23:23.183 --> 00:23:24.924
Why won't you let me in?

402
00:23:31.931 --> 00:23:35.413
You know why. I can't.

403
00:23:35.544 --> 00:23:37.807
Please.
just stay and talk with me.

404
00:23:37.937 --> 00:23:39.896
You said you liked me.

405
00:23:40.026 --> 00:23:42.115
I do!

406
00:23:42.246 --> 00:23:44.466
I can't keep coming here.

407
00:23:44.596 --> 00:23:47.817
knowing I'll see you
but never get to feel you.

408
00:23:47.947 --> 00:23:51.081
knowing you're afraid of me.

409
00:23:51.211 --> 00:23:52.909
that you're disgusted by me.

410
00:23:53.039 --> 00:23:54.737
No. It--

411
00:23:54.867 --> 00:23:57.130
You always tell me
how lonely you are in there.

412
00:23:57.261 --> 00:24:00.264
You have no idea
how lonely it is out here.

413
00:24:02.353 --> 00:24:04.834
It wasn't my choice
to be this way.

414
00:24:06.400 --> 00:24:08.054
Goodbye. Kevin.

415
00:24:08.185 --> 00:24:10.100
Wait. wait.

416
00:24:13.190 --> 00:24:17.150
You know. there's a party
going on downstairs.

417
00:24:17.281 --> 00:24:21.024
Everyone's having
a really good time.

418
00:24:21.154 --> 00:24:23.330
But you are the only one
that I want to be with.

419
00:24:23.461 --> 00:24:26.029
You are the only one
that I can really talk to.

420
00:24:31.687 --> 00:24:34.820
You promise it'll just be you?
No one else can get in?

421
00:24:35.821 --> 00:24:39.869
Not once we shut the window.
I promise.

422
00:24:43.002 --> 00:24:43.960
Okay.

423
00:24:55.058 --> 00:24:58.061
And now.
the question is...

424
00:25:01.107 --> 00:25:03.588
...how many
dimensions are there?

425
00:25:03.719 --> 00:25:07.418
Bosonic string theorists believe
there are 26 dimensions.

426
00:25:07.549 --> 00:25:10.595
but superstring theorists
say there's only 10.

427
00:25:10.726 --> 00:25:13.250
[Stacey] And is that what this
place is? Another dimension?

428
00:25:13.380 --> 00:25:14.686
[Dale] Oh. no. no.

429
00:25:14.817 --> 00:25:16.906
This is a pocket universe.

430
00:25:17.036 --> 00:25:18.081
Oh. my God.

431
00:25:19.430 --> 00:25:21.301
For Christ's sake. man. enough.

432
00:25:23.129 --> 00:25:25.001
It's not a pocket universe;

433
00:25:25.131 --> 00:25:26.393
it's not whatever
the fuck you think it is.

434
00:25:26.524 --> 00:25:28.004
and nobody gives a fuck.

435
00:25:28.134 --> 00:25:30.441
So why don't you
shut the fuck up. man?

436
00:25:30.572 --> 00:25:34.053
Yeah. okay. have another drink.

437
00:25:34.184 --> 00:25:36.839
All right. calm down.

438
00:25:38.275 --> 00:25:39.189
-[Glass smashes]
-Jesus!

439
00:25:39.319 --> 00:25:40.973
Hey!

440
00:25:41.104 --> 00:25:42.105
What are you
gonna do about it? Huh?

441
00:25:42.235 --> 00:25:43.062
-Hey!
-What are you gonna do?

442
00:25:43.193 --> 00:25:45.238
All right. okay.

443
00:25:45.369 --> 00:25:47.806
Take him upstairs before he
starts shooting up the place.

444
00:25:51.549 --> 00:25:53.333
-No. no. no. no!
-Hey. hey. hey! That's enough.

445
00:25:53.464 --> 00:25:55.379
That's enough!
Now. ease up!

446
00:25:57.511 --> 00:25:59.252
You okay?

447
00:25:59.383 --> 00:26:01.080
Hey. you okay?

448
00:26:05.084 --> 00:26:09.219
Yeah. I'm sorry. I. um--

449
00:26:09.349 --> 00:26:11.003
I'm just gonna go
upstairs and lay down.

450
00:26:11.134 --> 00:26:12.396
Okay.
I'll come with you.

451
00:26:12.526 --> 00:26:15.486
Nah. it's fine. It's fine.
Hey. I'm just. uh...

452
00:26:15.617 --> 00:26:19.055
[Sniffling. exhaling sharply]

453
00:26:19.185 --> 00:26:21.710
It's your night.

454
00:26:21.840 --> 00:26:23.233
Just stay.

455
00:26:31.241 --> 00:26:33.330
Goddamn animal.

456
00:26:33.460 --> 00:26:35.158
Like mother. like son.

457
00:26:39.684 --> 00:26:43.122
You stay the fuck
outta my sight.

458
00:26:52.131 --> 00:26:53.829
Now. close the window. quick.

459
00:27:01.532 --> 00:27:05.318
See?
Just the two of us.

460
00:27:05.449 --> 00:27:07.190
Just the two of us.

461
00:27:10.454 --> 00:27:12.369
My handsome boy.

462
00:27:12.499 --> 00:27:15.198
Your hands are so warm.

463
00:27:15.328 --> 00:27:17.156
Did you think
they would be cold?

464
00:27:20.507 --> 00:27:21.944
Kiss me.

465
00:27:39.265 --> 00:27:47.317
♪

466
00:27:49.101 --> 00:27:50.015
[Grunts]

467
00:27:51.582 --> 00:27:53.105
[Grunts]

468
00:27:54.280 --> 00:27:56.108
[Gasping]

469
00:27:56.239 --> 00:27:57.501
[Stammers]

470
00:27:57.631 --> 00:27:58.981
[Growls]

471
00:27:59.111 --> 00:28:00.199
[Knocking]

472
00:28:00.330 --> 00:28:01.374
What?

473
00:28:03.463 --> 00:28:05.204
[Sighs]
Dinner's ready.

474
00:28:05.335 --> 00:28:07.511
I'm not hungry.

475
00:28:07.641 --> 00:28:09.208
You've been staring
at that book

476
00:28:09.339 --> 00:28:10.557
for a day and a half.
maybe you should--

477
00:28:10.688 --> 00:28:12.342
Just fuck off.
Just fuck off.

478
00:28:12.472 --> 00:28:13.299
You know what. Jade?

479
00:28:13.430 --> 00:28:17.129
[Speaks Cantonese]

480
00:28:17.260 --> 00:28:18.261
Okay! Okay! Okay! Okay!

481
00:28:18.391 --> 00:28:20.437
I'm coming! Jesus!

482
00:28:21.525 --> 00:28:25.094
Uh. I wouldn't take too long
if I were you.

483
00:28:25.224 --> 00:28:26.748
[Speaks Cantonese]

484
00:28:31.796 --> 00:28:36.148
-[Indistinct chatter]
-[Music playing]

485
00:28:38.847 --> 00:28:40.762
You know. you should really
work on your party face.

486
00:28:42.894 --> 00:28:45.070
What are you doing.
sitting here all by yourself?

487
00:28:47.203 --> 00:28:50.162
You don't have to.

488
00:28:50.293 --> 00:28:53.122
I know you don't like me.

489
00:28:53.252 --> 00:28:54.253
That's not true.

490
00:28:56.647 --> 00:28:59.476
I just...

491
00:28:59.606 --> 00:29:01.608
It's such a nice party.

492
00:29:01.739 --> 00:29:04.350
You'll get one too.

493
00:29:05.525 --> 00:29:08.137
No.

494
00:29:08.267 --> 00:29:09.486
I don't think I will.

495
00:29:19.757 --> 00:29:21.193
Take off your shirt.

496
00:29:21.324 --> 00:29:23.456
What?

497
00:29:23.587 --> 00:29:26.198
I'm not gonna lie.
You drive me crazy sometimes.

498
00:29:28.461 --> 00:29:30.072
But we're in this together.

499
00:29:34.511 --> 00:29:36.121
You're not alone.

500
00:29:36.252 --> 00:29:38.167
Really?

501
00:29:43.563 --> 00:29:46.828
Think of it as an early gift
for your anniversary.

502
00:29:49.787 --> 00:29:51.615
You know what?

503
00:29:51.745 --> 00:29:54.444
Much as I hate to admit.
it looks better on you.

504
00:29:54.574 --> 00:29:57.490
[Laughs]
That's wildly untrue.

505
00:29:59.275 --> 00:30:01.016
But thank you.

506
00:30:05.934 --> 00:30:08.240
I'm gonna find something
to give you. too.

507
00:30:11.722 --> 00:30:14.420
Excuse me.

508
00:30:14.551 --> 00:30:16.161
That was nice of you.

509
00:30:18.207 --> 00:30:22.124
Everybody needs a little
pick-me-up sometimes.

510
00:30:23.386 --> 00:30:26.128
Can I ask you something?

511
00:30:26.258 --> 00:30:28.130
Sure.

512
00:30:28.260 --> 00:30:31.481
Uh. that girl that you--
that you kissed before?

513
00:30:31.611 --> 00:30:34.571
Who? Stacey?
Yeah. she's great.

514
00:30:34.701 --> 00:30:38.749
Yeah. I'm just-- I thought you
and Ellis were... together.

515
00:30:38.880 --> 00:30:40.707
Oh.
Oh. God. yeah. Yeah. no.

516
00:30:40.838 --> 00:30:42.796
Ellis. he's-- he's my person.

517
00:30:42.927 --> 00:30:46.409
That thing with Stacey. that's
just. you know. fooling around.

518
00:30:48.367 --> 00:30:50.195
Oh. okay.

519
00:30:52.110 --> 00:30:54.417
Do you think...

520
00:30:55.722 --> 00:30:57.550
Could I kiss you?

521
00:30:58.856 --> 00:31:00.597
Oh. um. Julie...

522
00:31:00.727 --> 00:31:03.382
No. I was-- I was just kidding.
I didn't mean--

523
00:31:03.513 --> 00:31:04.688
No. sweetie--

524
00:31:04.818 --> 00:31:06.298
No. you know what?
Just forget it.

525
00:31:07.430 --> 00:31:10.999
[Sighs]

526
00:31:11.129 --> 00:31:14.132
So. this girl tells you she's
hearing voices and you just--

527
00:31:14.263 --> 00:31:17.222
Look. I was skeptical.
Just like you. okay?

528
00:31:18.658 --> 00:31:21.748
But then...

529
00:31:21.879 --> 00:31:24.229
she showed me this.

530
00:31:24.360 --> 00:31:26.188
Look at that.

531
00:31:27.363 --> 00:31:28.451
That's the logo--

532
00:31:28.581 --> 00:31:29.713
I know what it is.

533
00:31:29.843 --> 00:31:31.628
That was almost
three years ago.

534
00:31:31.758 --> 00:31:34.544
Sara and Nathan have been here.
what? Four. five months?

535
00:31:34.674 --> 00:31:37.416
All right. so you told someone.
someone told Sara--

536
00:31:37.547 --> 00:31:38.983
I never told a soul.

537
00:31:39.114 --> 00:31:43.727
Boyd. there was no possible way
she could have known.

538
00:31:43.857 --> 00:31:45.555
Something was
watching me that day.

539
00:31:45.685 --> 00:31:47.557
the same thing that told Sara--

540
00:31:47.687 --> 00:31:49.733
And you think this thing
is trying to help us?

541
00:31:49.863 --> 00:31:52.649
By killing an old man
and a child?

542
00:31:52.779 --> 00:31:56.870
Whatever it is. it's a part
of the fabric of this place.

543
00:31:57.001 --> 00:31:58.872
Okay?
Whatever connection Sara has

544
00:31:59.003 --> 00:32:01.614
makes her valuable in ways
we may not even understand yet.

545
00:32:01.745 --> 00:32:03.834
Okay. now if you want to put
her in the box. that's fine.

546
00:32:03.965 --> 00:32:05.749
I'm not gonna stop you.

547
00:32:05.879 --> 00:32:09.492
But if you're serious
about finding answers -

548
00:32:09.622 --> 00:32:12.625
the fact that you're going on
this journey at the same time

549
00:32:12.756 --> 00:32:15.715
that this connection
is revealed.

550
00:32:15.846 --> 00:32:17.630
that's not just a coincidence.

551
00:32:17.761 --> 00:32:21.460
That's providence.

552
00:32:21.591 --> 00:32:24.463
So. what are you suggesting?

553
00:32:24.594 --> 00:32:27.771
That we go with you.
Sara and I. Okay?

554
00:32:27.901 --> 00:32:29.425
We use this connection
to our advantage.

555
00:32:30.643 --> 00:32:31.905
So. a priest. a sheriff.

556
00:32:32.036 --> 00:32:34.517
and a murdering psycho
walk into a bar.

557
00:32:34.647 --> 00:32:37.520
Yeah. something like that. yeah.

558
00:32:37.650 --> 00:32:39.435
-[Scoffs]
-What?

559
00:32:46.181 --> 00:32:47.312
[Gasps]

560
00:32:53.492 --> 00:32:56.626
[Whistles]

561
00:32:56.756 --> 00:33:00.021
If we go any deeper. we're
gonna need a taller ladder.

562
00:33:00.151 --> 00:33:04.373
[Sighs] Well. we'll go
as deep as we have to.

563
00:33:10.466 --> 00:33:11.510
[Exhales]

564
00:33:11.641 --> 00:33:14.600
Here. come here.

565
00:33:14.731 --> 00:33:15.688
Let me take
a look at that.

566
00:33:15.819 --> 00:33:16.776
I'm fine. really.

567
00:33:18.039 --> 00:33:20.954
"Fine" is not a word I would use

568
00:33:21.085 --> 00:33:24.523
to describe any of us
at this point.

569
00:33:31.878 --> 00:33:33.793
-Ow!
-That's it. Yeah.

570
00:33:33.924 --> 00:33:35.839
[Gasps]

571
00:33:35.969 --> 00:33:37.449
Yup.

572
00:33:37.580 --> 00:33:40.365
-Oof!
-Little bit harder?

573
00:33:40.496 --> 00:33:42.976
[Groans]

574
00:33:43.107 --> 00:33:46.719
Why don't you take a break?
Go sit with Ethan for a bit.

575
00:33:46.850 --> 00:33:48.895
I'll take over here.

576
00:33:49.026 --> 00:33:52.508
[Moans]
Are you stuck on your antenna?

577
00:33:52.638 --> 00:33:53.726
Yeah.

578
00:33:53.857 --> 00:33:55.163
Ow. Go slow. please.

579
00:33:55.293 --> 00:33:56.555
Pretty much.

580
00:33:58.992 --> 00:34:00.429
Oh. my God.

581
00:34:00.559 --> 00:34:01.560
How's that?

582
00:34:01.691 --> 00:34:04.346
It's amazing.

583
00:34:04.476 --> 00:34:06.522
[Exhales]

584
00:34:10.047 --> 00:34:13.442
[Breathes deeply]

585
00:34:24.017 --> 00:34:27.847
-[Indistinct chatter]
-[Music playing in distance]

586
00:34:38.641 --> 00:34:48.564
♪

587
00:35:29.082 --> 00:35:31.607
[Knocking]

588
00:35:36.699 --> 00:35:37.961
[Knocking]

589
00:35:46.796 --> 00:35:47.884
[Knocking]

590
00:35:50.974 --> 00:35:53.019
Can I come in?

591
00:35:53.150 --> 00:35:54.804
I'd rather you didn't.

592
00:35:54.934 --> 00:35:56.893
Please?

593
00:35:57.023 --> 00:35:59.504
This is the only place
in this house I can be alone.

594
00:35:59.635 --> 00:36:01.202
Well. sort of.

595
00:36:03.291 --> 00:36:04.988
-You look sad.
-Can I just come in?

596
00:36:05.118 --> 00:36:06.859
I'm having a really bad night.

597
00:36:12.952 --> 00:36:16.042
Are you going somewhere?
It looks like you're packing.

598
00:36:16.173 --> 00:36:19.568
No. I'm just...

599
00:36:19.698 --> 00:36:21.874
No.
It's hard to explain.

600
00:36:24.137 --> 00:36:25.791
Why did you dig
those graves?

601
00:36:28.229 --> 00:36:30.231
I don't want to talk about that.

602
00:36:34.409 --> 00:36:36.759
Are these from all the cars
that have come into town?

603
00:36:36.889 --> 00:36:38.630
Yes. that's right.

604
00:36:42.895 --> 00:36:43.896
On my first night.

605
00:36:44.027 --> 00:36:45.985
down by the pantry.

606
00:36:46.116 --> 00:36:48.249
you said that two cars hadn't
come to town on the same day

607
00:36:48.379 --> 00:36:52.470
for a really long time.
and that it was special.

608
00:36:52.601 --> 00:36:54.037
Why?

609
00:36:54.167 --> 00:36:57.083
You've been here
the longest out of anyone.

610
00:36:57.214 --> 00:36:59.956
Do you know what this place is?

611
00:37:09.313 --> 00:37:12.098
Seriously. man. I don't know why
you keep staring at that thing.

612
00:37:12.229 --> 00:37:13.970
I'm sorry. Hold on.

613
00:37:15.885 --> 00:37:18.540
This page. it's...

614
00:37:19.715 --> 00:37:21.499
[Kenny] What?

615
00:37:21.630 --> 00:37:24.285
There's two pages
stuck together here.

616
00:37:33.990 --> 00:37:35.731
Whoa. whoa. whoa. Okay.

617
00:37:35.861 --> 00:37:37.907
[Kenny] Huh.

618
00:37:38.037 --> 00:37:39.952
Now. we're talking.

619
00:37:46.742 --> 00:37:47.699
Victor!

620
00:37:49.788 --> 00:37:51.877
[Speaks Cantonese]

621
00:38:00.016 --> 00:38:01.974
Holy shit.

622
00:38:02.105 --> 00:38:03.802
-[Indistinct chatter]
-[Music playing]

623
00:38:03.933 --> 00:38:06.152
You're gonna go
to a new home now.

624
00:38:06.283 --> 00:38:08.546
I'm gonna give you to Fatima.

625
00:38:08.677 --> 00:38:11.810
She's gonna take
such good care of you.

626
00:38:11.941 --> 00:38:15.640
[Woman laughs]

627
00:38:15.771 --> 00:38:16.989
[Laughs]

628
00:38:18.164 --> 00:38:19.862
What are you laughing at?

629
00:38:21.820 --> 00:38:25.650
[Breathing rapidly]

630
00:38:25.781 --> 00:38:26.999
[Gasps]

631
00:38:27.130 --> 00:38:29.654
[Panicked whimpers]

632
00:38:29.785 --> 00:38:31.090
Hi. Trudy.

633
00:38:31.221 --> 00:38:33.049
How-- how do you know my name?

634
00:38:33.179 --> 00:38:34.964
We know all your names.

635
00:38:35.094 --> 00:38:37.619
[Gasps]

636
00:38:40.273 --> 00:38:43.668
[Breathing rapidly]

637
00:38:43.799 --> 00:38:44.887
[Gasping]

638
00:38:45.017 --> 00:38:47.629
[Screams]

639
00:38:47.759 --> 00:38:49.935
[Screams]

640
00:38:50.066 --> 00:38:51.850
[Stammering] I'm just saying...

641
00:38:54.070 --> 00:38:57.987
I've been here longer than him.
Deserve a little respect.

642
00:39:01.251 --> 00:39:02.992
I could really help this
place if they just--

643
00:39:03.122 --> 00:39:05.821
What the...?

644
00:39:05.951 --> 00:39:06.996
Is that blood?

645
00:39:07.126 --> 00:39:09.825
Jeez...

646
00:39:09.955 --> 00:39:11.653
What the...?

647
00:39:14.960 --> 00:39:16.788
Ah!

648
00:39:16.919 --> 00:39:18.355
[Blood-curdling scream]

649
00:39:18.486 --> 00:39:21.837
They're in the house!
They're inside!

650
00:39:23.621 --> 00:39:27.973
[Screaming]

651
00:39:35.067 --> 00:39:36.808
Ellis?
Have you seen Ellis?

652
00:39:40.072 --> 00:39:41.900
[Breathing rapidly]

653
00:39:42.031 --> 00:39:42.945
Ellis!

654
00:39:45.164 --> 00:39:46.165
[Woman] Follow protocol!

655
00:39:46.296 --> 00:39:47.863
[Man]
Where's the van?!

656
00:39:47.993 --> 00:39:49.125
Hide!

657
00:39:49.255 --> 00:39:50.256
-[Screams]
-What's going on?

658
00:39:50.387 --> 00:39:51.562
It's starting.

659
00:39:51.693 --> 00:39:52.868
What?
What's starting?

660
00:39:52.998 --> 00:39:53.825
We have to go.

661
00:39:53.956 --> 00:39:55.261
Go where?

662
00:39:55.392 --> 00:39:57.742
Where are we going?

663
00:39:57.873 --> 00:39:59.875
Go where? Hello?

664
00:40:00.005 --> 00:40:03.226
[Breathing rapidly]
Answer me!

665
00:40:03.356 --> 00:40:05.097
[Breathing rapidly]

666
00:40:05.228 --> 00:40:07.143
[Screaming in distance]

667
00:40:07.273 --> 00:40:10.842
[Grunts]
You go first.

668
00:40:10.973 --> 00:40:13.018
I'll follow you down.

669
00:40:13.149 --> 00:40:15.238
Here. Take this.

670
00:40:15.368 --> 00:40:18.023
[Whimpering]

671
00:40:18.154 --> 00:40:22.767
[Screaming in distance]

672
00:40:22.898 --> 00:40:24.029
You ready?

673
00:40:26.902 --> 00:40:30.079
[Breathing rapidly]

674
00:40:30.209 --> 00:40:32.081
[Whimpering]

675
00:40:32.211 --> 00:40:35.171
[Screaming indistinctly]

676
00:40:35.301 --> 00:40:37.260
[Indistinct panic. screaming]

677
00:40:37.390 --> 00:40:39.131
[Screaming]

678
00:40:39.262 --> 00:40:40.916
Follow protocol!

679
00:40:41.046 --> 00:40:44.006
Find your buddy!
Get into the van! Come on!

680
00:40:44.136 --> 00:40:45.964
Wait. Donna!
What are you doing?

681
00:40:46.095 --> 00:40:48.271
-Where's Ellis and Julie?
-I don't know.

682
00:40:48.401 --> 00:40:49.925
-Hey. Donna!
-I am not running.

683
00:40:50.055 --> 00:40:51.317
Okay. You've gotta get
those people to town.

684
00:40:51.448 --> 00:40:52.667
Save as many as you can.

685
00:40:52.797 --> 00:40:54.016
-Follow protocol.
-Okay. okay.

686
00:40:54.146 --> 00:40:56.409
[People screaming]

687
00:40:56.540 --> 00:40:58.150
All right. everyone.
Out of the way.

688
00:40:58.281 --> 00:40:59.674
Get in the van!

689
00:40:59.804 --> 00:41:03.155
[Indistinct panic. screaming]

690
00:41:07.290 --> 00:41:10.075
Oh. my God.

691
00:41:10.206 --> 00:41:11.337
[Anguished scream]

692
00:41:11.468 --> 00:41:12.991
Oh. my God. Hurry up!

693
00:41:13.122 --> 00:41:15.690
[Woman screaming]

694
00:41:17.126 --> 00:41:19.389
[Grunts]

695
00:41:19.520 --> 00:41:20.999
We need to get to town.

696
00:41:21.130 --> 00:41:22.871
[Breathing heavily]

697
00:41:25.526 --> 00:41:28.006
-No. We have to go to the trees.
-Are you crazy?

698
00:41:28.137 --> 00:41:29.181
Those things live in there!

699
00:41:29.312 --> 00:41:30.356
-Please!
-They'll kill us!

700
00:41:30.487 --> 00:41:32.315
You have to trust me.

701
00:41:32.445 --> 00:41:34.012
If you want to see
your family again.

702
00:41:34.143 --> 00:41:35.797
we have to go to the trees.

703
00:41:35.927 --> 00:41:36.928
Okay.

704
00:41:38.539 --> 00:41:40.236
[Screaming in distance]

705
00:41:43.326 --> 00:41:45.067
[Shouting in distance]

706
00:41:51.247 --> 00:41:53.205
[Woman in distance] No!

707
00:41:53.336 --> 00:41:56.078
[Shouting and screaming
in distance]

708
00:41:56.208 --> 00:41:58.036
[Breathing unsteadily]

709
00:41:58.167 --> 00:42:02.563
[Screaming in distance]

710
00:42:12.355 --> 00:42:15.271
[Breathing unsteadily]

711
00:42:17.926 --> 00:42:23.148
♪

712
00:42:23.279 --> 00:42:25.324
[Dripping]

713
00:42:25.455 --> 00:42:35.421
♪

714
00:42:35.552 --> 00:42:39.208
[Breathing unsteadily]

715
00:42:39.338 --> 00:42:40.383
No.

716
00:42:47.085 --> 00:42:49.261
[Sniffling]
No.

717
00:42:49.392 --> 00:42:51.263
Baby. no way.

718
00:42:57.400 --> 00:43:00.882
[Floor creaking]

719
00:43:12.502 --> 00:43:14.286
[Man in distance]
Keep moving!

720
00:43:14.417 --> 00:43:16.288
[Screaming indistinctly]

721
00:43:19.291 --> 00:43:20.945
[Grunts]

722
00:43:22.294 --> 00:43:23.252
Ellis!

723
00:43:23.382 --> 00:43:24.906
[Coughs]

724
00:43:25.036 --> 00:43:26.124
Hey.

725
00:43:26.255 --> 00:43:28.344
Hi.
Have you seen Julie?

726
00:43:28.474 --> 00:43:29.606
I don't know. I can't--

727
00:43:29.737 --> 00:43:31.303
-[Screaming]
-Okay. we need to go.

728
00:43:31.434 --> 00:43:32.827
We need to run.
Come on!

729
00:43:32.957 --> 00:43:35.394
-Come on.
-[Woman screaming]

730
00:43:35.525 --> 00:43:37.092
[Shouts in pain]
No. I can't!

731
00:43:37.222 --> 00:43:38.484
-Come on!
-I can't go! You just go.

732
00:43:38.615 --> 00:43:40.443
I'm not going without you!
Come on. we can do this.

733
00:43:40.573 --> 00:43:42.314
Up. up. up!

734
00:43:42.445 --> 00:43:44.490
Up. up. up! We have to
get back in the house!

735
00:43:44.621 --> 00:43:46.275
We have to get inside!
I have an idea. Come on.

736
00:43:54.109 --> 00:43:55.501
Please!

737
00:43:55.632 --> 00:43:57.286
Please. please. please. please!
Please. Please...

738
00:43:57.416 --> 00:43:58.635
[Banging]

739
00:43:58.766 --> 00:44:00.202
[Woman inside]
Don't be like that.

740
00:44:00.332 --> 00:44:03.422
We were having
so much fun.

741
00:44:04.641 --> 00:44:06.382
[Footsteps receding]

742
00:44:06.512 --> 00:44:09.777
[Breathing unsteadily]

743
00:44:09.907 --> 00:44:12.170
[Thudding]

744
00:44:12.301 --> 00:44:14.259
[Sobbing]

745
00:44:14.390 --> 00:44:17.175
[Banging]

746
00:44:17.306 --> 00:44:19.438
-[Thudding]
-[Doorknob rattling]

747
00:44:19.569 --> 00:44:23.181
[Sobbing]

748
00:44:23.312 --> 00:44:24.356
[Doorknob rattling]

749
00:44:24.487 --> 00:44:29.187
[Footsteps thudding]

750
00:44:29.318 --> 00:44:31.276
[Breathing unsteadily]

751
00:44:31.407 --> 00:44:34.192
[Thudding inside house]

752
00:44:38.022 --> 00:44:40.155
How'd you know
that was gonna work?

753
00:44:40.285 --> 00:44:41.504
I didn't.

754
00:44:44.376 --> 00:44:46.117
With your dad
and the RV I just--

755
00:44:49.599 --> 00:44:53.385
[Sobbing]

756
00:44:59.957 --> 00:45:01.219
I'm sorry.

757
00:45:06.485 --> 00:45:08.749
I love you.

758
00:45:11.577 --> 00:45:13.492
I love you too.

759
00:45:23.546 --> 00:45:26.288
[Grunting in pain]

760
00:45:30.379 --> 00:45:32.381
-[Julie] Where are we going?!
-There's another one here.

761
00:45:32.511 --> 00:45:34.122
-[Julie] Another what?
-Come on.

762
00:45:34.252 --> 00:45:35.688
You have to get inside.

763
00:45:35.819 --> 00:45:37.908
-The tree? No! No!
-You'll be safe!

764
00:45:38.039 --> 00:45:39.605
-What?
-I promise.

765
00:45:39.736 --> 00:45:41.477
You have to find your brother.
You have to warn him.

766
00:45:41.607 --> 00:45:43.218
You have to tell
him it's starting.

767
00:45:43.348 --> 00:45:44.393
I don't know what
you're talking about!

768
00:45:44.523 --> 00:45:46.177
He will.

769
00:45:46.308 --> 00:45:47.962
-Go. go. go!
-No. wait!

770
00:45:48.092 --> 00:45:50.268
[Victor]
I'll be right behind you.

771
00:45:50.399 --> 00:45:55.317
[Door creaks]

772
00:45:55.447 --> 00:46:00.104
[Panicked breathing]

773
00:46:01.497 --> 00:46:05.544
♪

774
00:46:05.675 --> 00:46:08.417
If we do this -
and I mean "if" -

775
00:46:08.547 --> 00:46:11.202
and she even
blinks the wrong way...

776
00:46:11.333 --> 00:46:13.683
You do what you need to do.

777
00:46:13.814 --> 00:46:17.208
But we're goin' out there
and we're gonna find answers.

778
00:46:17.339 --> 00:46:18.862
We're gonna find a way. Boyd.

779
00:46:18.993 --> 00:46:21.647
This. this is why I was told
to get back in the car.

780
00:46:21.778 --> 00:46:24.694
So that you and I

781
00:46:24.825 --> 00:46:28.437
can go out there and find a way
to bring these people home.

782
00:46:28.567 --> 00:46:30.352
You're a fucking madman.
You know that. right?

783
00:46:30.482 --> 00:46:32.615
Bible's full of 'em.

784
00:46:32.745 --> 00:46:36.314
-[Chuckle]
-[Car horn blaring]

785
00:46:36.445 --> 00:46:37.620
What the fuck?

786
00:46:37.750 --> 00:46:40.362
[Car horn blaring]

787
00:46:40.492 --> 00:46:41.363
What happened?!

788
00:46:42.625 --> 00:46:44.322
I-- what happened?!

789
00:46:44.453 --> 00:46:45.584
They got in and they--

790
00:46:45.715 --> 00:46:46.803
-Wait! Where's Ellis?
-I don't know!

791
00:46:46.934 --> 00:46:48.544
-Where is Ellis?
-I don't know! Sorry!

792
00:46:48.674 --> 00:46:50.328
Everybody inside.
Everybody inside.

793
00:46:50.459 --> 00:46:51.895
-Go! Let's go!
-Everybody inside now!

794
00:46:52.026 --> 00:46:54.419
-Let's go! Let's go! Hustle!
-Keep going! Keep going!

795
00:46:54.550 --> 00:46:56.595
-Let's go! Come on. man!
-Hurry. hurry. hurry! Inside!

796
00:46:56.726 --> 00:46:58.467
-Is that it? Is that it?
-Inside. everybody!

797
00:46:58.597 --> 00:46:59.729
[Man] Where are you guys going?

798
00:46:59.860 --> 00:47:01.165
You guys okay over there?

799
00:47:01.296 --> 00:47:02.471
[Woman] Father...

800
00:47:02.601 --> 00:47:04.429
[Boyd] No!

801
00:47:04.560 --> 00:47:06.344
-No. come here!
-[Gun firing]

802
00:47:08.781 --> 00:47:10.348
Close it!

803
00:47:10.479 --> 00:47:12.176
Come on.
You got it.

804
00:47:12.307 --> 00:47:14.570
[Groaning]
Come on!

805
00:47:14.700 --> 00:47:16.311
[Donna] Keep him elevated.

806
00:47:16.441 --> 00:47:18.400
Get me something
to stop the bleeding!

807
00:47:18.530 --> 00:47:19.792
-Please. no.
-[Boyd] Okay. it's okay.

808
00:47:19.923 --> 00:47:21.533
-Please!
-Let me stop the bleeding!

809
00:47:21.664 --> 00:47:23.231
Please... No.

810
00:47:23.361 --> 00:47:24.449
-You're okay.
-No.

811
00:47:24.580 --> 00:47:26.277
-You're okay.
-No...

812
00:47:26.408 --> 00:47:29.280
You're okay.
You are okay.

813
00:47:29.411 --> 00:47:31.326
It doesn't end like this.

814
00:47:31.456 --> 00:47:32.457
Right.

815
00:47:32.588 --> 00:47:34.372
My path...
Please!

816
00:47:34.503 --> 00:47:36.374
Hurry up!

817
00:47:36.505 --> 00:47:37.201
[Wheezing]

818
00:47:37.332 --> 00:47:38.507
Okay.

819
00:47:38.637 --> 00:47:40.248
I got him.

820
00:47:40.378 --> 00:47:41.379
One...

821
00:47:42.554 --> 00:47:44.295
There we go.
There we go.

822
00:47:44.426 --> 00:47:45.209
Open your eyes.
Stay with me.

823
00:47:45.340 --> 00:47:46.558
Stay with me.

824
00:47:46.689 --> 00:47:48.865
[Groaning] Pray with me.

825
00:47:48.996 --> 00:47:50.475
-[Boyd] What? Okay.
-Pray with me.

826
00:47:50.606 --> 00:47:52.521
-Okay.
-Pray with me.

827
00:47:52.651 --> 00:47:54.218
Okay. okay.

828
00:47:54.349 --> 00:47:55.567
Our Father.

829
00:47:55.698 --> 00:47:59.528
[Both] ...who art in Heaven.

830
00:47:59.658 --> 00:48:01.704
hallowed be thy name.

831
00:48:01.834 --> 00:48:05.795
Thy kingdom come.
thy will be done

832
00:48:05.926 --> 00:48:08.711
on earth
as it is in heaven.

833
00:48:08.841 --> 00:48:11.714
Give us this day
our daily bread...

834
00:48:11.844 --> 00:48:13.368
[Wheezing]

835
00:48:13.498 --> 00:48:15.587
...and forgive us
our trespasses

836
00:48:15.718 --> 00:48:19.330
as we forgive those
who trespass against us.

837
00:48:19.461 --> 00:48:21.506
And lead us not into temptation.

838
00:48:21.637 --> 00:48:26.250
but deliver us from evil.

839
00:48:27.817 --> 00:48:29.558
Amen.

840
00:48:29.688 --> 00:48:32.213
Amen.
[Breathing unsteadily]

841
00:48:32.343 --> 00:48:33.779
Amen.

842
00:48:33.910 --> 00:48:38.262
[Breathing unsteadily]

843
00:48:42.658 --> 00:48:52.711
♪
